{"type": "article", "id": 34379, "title": "和这些座椅搭配，读书也变得更有趣了｜这个设计了不起", "description": "每个周末，《好奇心日报》都会找个主题为你寻找精彩设计。", "date": "2016-11-11T23:11:12Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 266, "name": "椅子"}, {"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 1672, "name": "沙发"}, {"id": 34809, "name": "TILT"}, {"id": 34810, "name": "Atelier010"}, {"id": 34811, "name": "Nobody and Co."}, {"id": 34812, "name": "Lukas Avenas"}, {"id": 34813, "name": "元木大輔"}, {"id": 34814, "name": "Remi Van Oers"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 18, "praise_count": 494, "image": "img/article/article_show/201611111639407QB9uewyzntM5mp4.jpg", "contents": "<p class=\"\">          </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><p class=\"\">书架、茶几、边桌，或是地板，书籍最后的落脚处似乎总是离我们有一些距离。为了让书迷们能够和爱书们更加亲近，不少设计师在将多种家具功能融合在一起这件事上动起了脑筋。本周我们就挑选了其中一些有趣的尝试。阅读愉快。</p><p>          </p><h3>14 by Lukas Avenas</h3><p>立陶宛工业设计师 <a href=\"http://lukasavenas.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lukas Avenas</a> 带来的 <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/gallery/22554107/14\" rel=\"nofollow\">14</a> 就像是杂志架和椅子的结合体：它的结构相当简洁但并不对称，只有一边设计成了可以当做书签使用的分隔架。从侧面看去，座椅本身也并非水平而是微微后倾。这样一把椅子看起来很像是会放在理发店休息区的那种，放在普通的居家环境中也很合适。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164039ENbVuOmLozA1wcgT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667500\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164039riQ1EMlnbCD09Nf8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164039QohUF1Dc3XWPCgjH.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.473750\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164039y2KkBATH7WbDg09j.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.473750\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Open Book by TILT</h3><p>设计工作室 <a href=\"http://studiotilt.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">TILT</a> 带来的 Open Book 更像是一张沙发，被包围的感觉和飞机头等舱的座位有些相似。它的一侧由几个置物格构成，同时还可以当做边桌使用。另一边则被木板包裹起来，上面还附有延伸到座椅背面的杂志架，足以满足日常的收纳需要。因为整合了多种家具功能，这张座椅给人一种坐在私人迷你图书馆的感觉，好像一旦窝进去就很难再出来了。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164107JbvyHpw1AFcYhxDC.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.196610\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164106UgmWy8xXZCuji1hn.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.361667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201611111641061HN5PVM6xrYpSXwU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.336667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164107OGrCjWgYmK4QD5BP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.348333\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Lost in Sofa by Daisuke Motogi</h3><p>如果你有在沙发的犄角旮旯里翻出钱币之类陈年旧物的经历，那或许会明白日本设计师<a href=\"http://www.dskmtg.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">元木大輔</a>为什么要将这件设计取名叫“迷失沙发”（<a href=\"http://www.dskmtg.com/work/l_sofa.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lost in Sofa</a>）。它的坐垫被细分成一个个小的立方体，像是用灰色的小砖块砌成的。你可以往缝隙中插入书本、遥控器或是装饰品——当然，还是得小心不要真的把小东西放进去找不着了。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164136Lsx7kfm16jiNCOao.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.142361\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164136zHxk9BhTM7bnlJwr.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201611111641367RXuIYQtExajPqyB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.905952\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Bibliochaise by Nobody and Co.</h3><p>意大利设计公司 <a href=\"http://www.nobodyandco.it/?lang=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nobody and Co.</a> 带来的 <a href=\"http://www.nobodyandco.it/?page_id=7858&amp;lang=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bibliochaise</a> 是一张想用码得整整齐齐的书籍把你包围起来的椅子。它的座椅被安置在一个栅栏结构的底座上，允许你随心所欲地把书放进矩形的格子中。通过座位下方暗藏的滚轮，它还可以载着书一道变换位置。公司还为 Bibliochaise 设计了配套的矮凳 Bibliopouf，两款设计的坐垫和底座颜色都可以进行订制。它们目前都只能在<a href=\"http://www.nobodyandco.it/?p=8495&amp;lang=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">实体店</a>内购买。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164153k6tdpb4NEru95lUw.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.328967\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164153y8RJ2zCc4AuhKxOG.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.331878\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164153vysroL4BIHlJ9TmM.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.328967\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201611111641548MxS1bm34KTYdwD6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.789655\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Reading Furniture by Remi Van Oers</h3><p>          </p><p>房子小放不进书架？荷兰设计师 <a href=\"http://www.remivanoers.nl/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Remi Van Oers</a> 为此设计了这套名为 Reading Furniture 的家具，其中最吸引人的就是自带收纳空间的椅子和可以放书的落地灯了。除此之外，Van Oers 还设计了一张将灯融合进椅背的椅子，美中不足之处在于灯的位置并不能移动。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164228Kqel6ODWptLAcfNj.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.607692\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164227jPo8OqRVlaYFTIhd.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.516667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164227SsTHh1oYj8KwlryQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.721538\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201611111642277NidHF3kyBj5nUYS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.813846\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164228NL1XoIMYATmJw8Qa.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.701538\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164228PZb4dONv6q7VrU2i.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.510769\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Bookworm by Atelier010</h3><p>          </p><p>如果你觉得上面的那些设计中规中矩了点，荷兰设计工作室 <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Atelier010\" rel=\"nofollow\">Atelier010</a> 带来的 Bookworm 会是一个让你眼前一亮的特例。它的造型相当独特，就像是一个用书构成的“茧”，附带的灯泡从顶端的小孔垂下，让你可以捧着书舒舒服服地躺在里面。如果你对它感兴趣的话，可以通过<a href=\"http://bookworm-bookshelf.nl/\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>了解具体规格和购买信息，“茧”的内、外圈颜色都可以单独订制。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164256IXKSgPtzy3eadh7q.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164256bGB65Whwg3IqCTuP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667557\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164256rnGc6lN8YR13Huv0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20161111164257RAT4Y5GrZzgFa1DH.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}